foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: Although DOI indicated in its FY 2007 Annual Report that there were 876 requests pending at the end of the fiscal year, the figure denoted in V.A. is correct. The difference is attributed to the fact that 1) although many requests were completed in FY 2007, the bureaus did not show them as being completed until after the FY 2007 report was finalized; 2) there were a few discrepancies in accounting; and 3) a few offices were not using the electronic FOIA tracking system and the numbers reported were inaccurate.

foia:ProcessedResponseTimeSection.foia:FootnoteText: Median and average number of days for the agency overall do not include figures reported for BIA, OIG, SOL, and one NPS region as they are not currently using DOI's electronic tracking system (applies to all sections of the report requesting the median/average number of days). This will be corrected in FY09.

DOI uses four tracks to process requests: Simple, Normal, Complex, and Expedited. The Normal track (not represented in this report) is used for those requests that can be processed within 20 workdays.

Figures reported under Section VII include both perfected and non-perfected requests. DOI is in the process of making updates to the electronic FOIA tracking system to capture data for perfected requests only.
